{"id":"merib-baal","term":"Merib-baal","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Contender with Baal, (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:34\">1 Chr. 8:34</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 9:40\">9:40</a>), elsewhere called Mephibosheth (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 4:4\">2 Sam. 4:4</a>), the son of Jonathan.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 8:34","1 Chronicles 9:40","2 Samuel 4:4"]}